 species have percolated into forest interiors. Native and alien diversity in edge plots were not related. Almost half the alien species belonged to three families and 85% were native to Eurasia. Our results suggest that alien species are moving into parks along road corridors and that elevation and land use of the matrix influence these invasion processes. Our findings corroborate the importance of early detection and control of invasive species in protected areas and highlight the importance of considering surrounding matrix land use in developing conservation strategies for reserves.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Pauchard, An\u00edbal", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Alaback, Paul B.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "Chapter 5", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/a73a82d5e6069a5d2a61fde84a7c2127", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/37fd9e4450ed70405308060900af25902afcd9cb0f7c92ae0cb88a47a4893a78", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/VXB8Q4HK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/VXB8Q4HK", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/b79e4fcfebf578895353c7ba22874284!/b29416-31579", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.1111/j.1523-1739.2004.00300.x", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.7430682", "relation": "isCitedBy", "resource_type": "publication-report", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "s